Summary: CrowdStrike (CRWD) faces direct risk from 2 analyzed bills, with impacts including a €15M fine and $90M subsidy; overall direct risk: -0.097; no indirect impacts.
SummaryKeypoints: H.R. 1 - One Big Beautiful Bill Act provides $90,000,000 in subsidy. affecting operations in United States. with short-term implementation The legislation states: "$90,000,000 for APEX Accelerators, the Mentor-Protege Program, and cybersecurity support to small non-traditional contractors;"

REGULATION (EU) 2024/1689 OF THE EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT AND OF THE COUNCIL establishes €15,000,000 fine. affecting operations in European Union. with short-term implementation The legislation states: "The Commission may impose on providers of general-purpose AI models fines not exceeding 3 % of their annual total worldwide turnover in the preceding financial year or EUR 15 000 000, whichever is higher."
